about.summary: R's default conflict management system gives the most recently loaded package precedence. This can make it hard to detect conflicts,  particularly when they arise because a package update creates ambiguity that did not previously exist. 'conflicted' takes a different approach,  making every conflict an error and forcing you to choose which function  to use.

name: r-conflicted
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.1.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-conflicted
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/conflicted_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/conflicted/conflicted_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 24fa24cd1d9a5c5c47a8976622d2c07a8a4db4aec5387b41e52865124256e9e1

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-memoise
    - r-rlang
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-memoise
    - r-rlang

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('conflicted')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('conflicted')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/r-lib/conflicted
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: R's default conflict management system gives the most recently loaded package precedence. This can make it hard to detect conflicts,  particularly when they arise because a package update creates ambiguity that did not previously exist. 'conflicted' takes a different approach,  making every conflict an error and
    forcing you to choose which function  to use.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
